<!-- FAQ                                                -->
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="section">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Common Questions</div>
  <h2>Power Platform Consulting — Answered</h2>

  <div class="faq-list">

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>What does a Power Platform consultant actually do?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          A Power Platform consultant designs, builds, and deploys custom business
          solutions using Microsoft's low-code tools — Power Apps, Power Automate,
          Power BI, and Copilot Studio. Unlike a generalist IT consultant, we focus
          specifically on translating your operational problems into working systems:
          automated workflows, custom applications, AI agents, and dashboards that
          connect to your existing Microsoft 365 environment.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do you work with businesses outside of Tulsa and Oklahoma?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          Yes — FlowNova works with clients across the US. We're headquartered in
          Tulsa, Oklahoma, but Power Platform work is remote-first by design.
          Discovery calls, architecture sessions, and delivery all happen over Teams.
          Most of our clients never need us on-site.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>What's the difference between Power Apps and Power Automate?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          Power Apps is where you build the interface — the form, the dashboard, the
          tool your team interacts with. Power Automate is the engine running in the
          background — handling approvals, sending notifications, syncing data, and
          triggering actions. In most real-world solutions, they work together: Power
          Apps surfaces the experience, Power Automate does the heavy lifting behind it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do I need a large IT team to get value from Power Platform?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          No. Most of FlowNova's clients are mid-sized businesses with lean IT teams
          or none at all. Power Platform operates within your existing Microsoft 365
          licenses — no new infrastructure required. We handle the architecture and
          build, then document and train your team so they can own it going forward.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How is FlowNova different from a large Microsoft partner?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p>
          Large partners typically deploy teams of junior consultants managed by senior
          account leads you rarely talk to. At FlowNova, you work directly with the
          engineer building your solution — no handoffs, no middlemen. That means faster
          discovery, tighter scoping, and builds that actually reflect your real workflow
          rather than a templated assumption about it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>

  </div>
</div>

